[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: Real-Time Co-Simulation Framework Requirements
OPTIONS:
  REQUIREMENT_STYLE: Table

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-FRAMEWORK
TITLE: Real-Time Co-Simulation Framework
STATEMENT: >
  The system shall be a real-time co-simulation framework developed in Rust,
  utilizing the Tokio runtime for asynchronous task management.

[GROUP]
TITLE: FMU Co-Simulation
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-FMU-SUPPORT
TITLE: FMU Co-Simulation Support
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall support the co-simulation of Functional Mockup Units (FMUs)
  compliant with the FMI standard for Co-Simulation.
STATUS: Blocked (due to unstable Rust FMI crate)
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-FMU-LOADING
TITLE: Dynamic FMU Loading
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall be able to dynamically load FMU binaries (.so or .dll) at runtime from a specified path.
REFINES: REQ-FMU-SUPPORT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-FMI-VERSION
TITLE: FMI Standard Version
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall support at least FMI 2.0 for Co-Simulation. Support for FMI 3.0 is a future goal.
REFINES: REQ-FMU-SUPPORT

[/GROUP]

[GROUP]
TITLE: Scheduling and Execution
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-SCHEDULING
TITLE: Real-Time Task Scheduling
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall schedule and execute simulation tasks in a pseudo-real-time manner, driven by the Tokio runtime.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-PERIODIC-TASKS
TITLE: Periodic Task Execution
STATEMENT: >
  FMUs and other simulation components (e.g., I/O tasks) shall be scheduled as periodic tasks with user-configurable execution rates.
REFINES: REQ-SCHEDULING

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-TIME-STEP-CONTROL
TITLE: Simulation Time Step Control
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall allow for user-configurable global simulation time steps,
  and manage the execution of periodic tasks and FMUs accordingly.
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-MULTI-CORE
TITLE: Multi-Core / Parallel Execution Support
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall leverage multi-core processors to execute independent
  simulation tasks and FMUs in parallel, optimizing performance for complex scenarios.
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-DATA-DEPENDENCY
TITLE: Data Dependency Management
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall manage data dependencies between interconnected simulation components (e.g., FMUs, I/O tasks).

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-EXECUTION-ORDER
TITLE: Automatic Execution Order Inference
STATEMENT: >
  Based on the configured data dependencies, the framework shall automatically infer the correct execution order for all tasks within a single time step using topological sorting.
REFINES: REQ-DATA-DEPENDENCY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-CAUSALITY-RESOLUTION
TITLE: Causality Problem Resolution
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall detect causal loops (algebraic cycles) in the dependency graph and report them to the user.
REFINES: REQ-DATA-DEPENDENCY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-MEMORY-BLOCKS
TITLE: Memory Blocks for Loop Breaking
STATEMENT: >
  Causal loops shall be resolvable by configuring specific data links to use a "memory" block, which introduces a one-step delay (z^-1), effectively breaking the cycle.
REFINES: REQ-CAUSALITY-RESOLUTION

[/GROUP]

[GROUP]
TITLE: I/O Subsystem
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-IO-SUBSYSTEM
TITLE: Input/Output Subsystem
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall provide a flexible and extensible I/O subsystem for interaction with hardware and external systems.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-IO-GPIO
TITLE: GPIO Task
STATEMENT: >
  The I/O subsystem shall include a task for digital General-Purpose Input/Output (GPIO) on supported platforms (e.g., Raspberry Pi).
REFINES: REQ-IO-SUBSYSTEM

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-IO-SERIAL
TITLE: Serial Communication Task
STATEMENT: >
  The I/O subsystem shall include a task for serial communication (e.g., UART, RS-232/485) with configurable parameters (baud rate, parity, etc.).
REFINES: REQ-IO-SUBSYSTEM

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-IO-UDP
TITLE: UDP Communication Task
STATEMENT: >
  The I/O subsystem shall include a task for sending and receiving data via the UDP protocol.
STATUS: Implemented
REFINES: REQ-IO-SUBSYSTEM

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-IO-ANALOG
TITLE: Analog Input/Output Tasks
STATEMENT: >
  The I/O subsystem shall include tasks for configurable analog input and output,
  supporting various voltage and current ranges, for interfacing with analog sensors and actuators.
STATUS: Implemented
REFINES: REQ-IO-SUBSYSTEM

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-IO-EXTENSIBILITY
TITLE: Extensible I/O
STATEMENT: >
  The I/O subsystem shall be designed with a trait-based API to allow new I/O task types to be added with minimal effort.
STATUS: Implemented
REFINES: REQ-IO-SUBSYSTEM

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-IO-INDUSTRIAL-PROTOCOLS
TITLE: Industrial Communication Protocols
STATEMENT: >
  The I/O subsystem shall support common industrial communication protocols
  (e.g., CAN, EtherCAT, Modbus TCP/RTU) to facilitate integration with
  a wide range of industrial hardware and control systems.
STATUS: Implemented (placeholder for Modbus TCP)
REFINES: REQ-IO-SUBSYSTEM

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-IO-SYNCHRONIZED
TITLE: Synchronized I/O
STATEMENT: >
  The I/O subsystem shall support synchronized data acquisition and output across
  multiple channels and different I/O types, ensuring precise timing and correlation
  of data.
STATUS: Implemented
REFINES: REQ-IO-SUBSYSTEM

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-IO-HIGH-SPEED-DAQ
TITLE: High-Speed Data Acquisition
STATEMENT: >
  The I/O subsystem shall be capable of high-speed data acquisition and generation
  for critical signals, with configurable sampling rates to meet demanding
  real-time simulation requirements.
STATUS: Implemented (placeholder)
REFINES: REQ-IO-SUBSYSTEM

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-IO-HIGH-SPEED-DAQ
TITLE: High-Speed Data Acquisition
STATEMENT: >
  The I/O subsystem shall be capable of high-speed data acquisition and generation
  for critical signals, with configurable sampling rates to meet demanding
  real-time simulation requirements.
REFINES: REQ-IO-SUBSYSTEM

[/GROUP]

[GROUP]
TITLE: Configuration
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

UID: REQ-CONFIGURATION
TITLE: Simulation Configuration
STATEMENT: >
  The entire simulation scenario, including FMUs, task scheduling, data dependencies, and I/O, shall be defined in a single, user-provided configuration file.
STATUS: Implemented
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-CONFIG-FORMAT
TITLE: Configuration File Format
STATEMENT: >
  The configuration shall use a human-readable, structured format. TOML is the preferred format.
STATUS: Implemented
REFINES: REQ-CONFIGURATION

[/GROUP]

[GROUP]
TITLE: Simulation Control & Data
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-SIM-LIFECYCLE
TITLE: Simulation Lifecycle Management
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall provide clear and accessible mechanisms to control the simulation lifecycle,
  including starting, stopping, pausing, and resuming simulation execution.
STATUS: Implemented
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-DATA-LOGGING
TITLE: Data Logging
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall provide configurable mechanisms for logging simulation data,
  including FMU variable values and I/O states, to persistent storage.
  The logging format shall be user-selectable (e.g., CSV, HDF5).
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-REALTIME-MONITORING
TITLE: Real-time Monitoring
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall provide interfaces or mechanisms for real-time monitoring
  of simulation progress and key variable values, suitable for visualization
  or debugging purposes.
STATUS: Implemented
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-TIME-SYNCHRONIZATION
TITLE: Time Synchronization
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall provide mechanisms to synchronize simulation time with wall-clock time,
  or to allow running simulations faster or slower than real-time, as configured by the user.
STATUS: Implemented
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[/GROUP]

[GROUP]
TITLE: Performance & Robustness
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-DETERMINISTIC-EXECUTION
TITLE: Deterministic Execution
STATEMENT: >
  For a given simulation configuration and identical inputs, the framework shall
  produce deterministic and repeatable simulation results across multiple runs.
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-ERROR-HANDLING
TITLE: Error Handling and Recovery
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall implement robust error handling for FMU execution failures,
  I/O errors, and other runtime issues, providing options for graceful shutdown
  or configurable recovery mechanisms.
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-PERFORMANCE-METRICS
TITLE: Performance Metrics
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall be capable of reporting key performance metrics, such as
  task execution times, jitter, and CPU utilization, to aid in performance analysis
  and optimization.
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-HARD-REALTIME
TITLE: Hard Real-Time Capability
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall be designed to support hard real-time execution on a
  Linux operating system with a real-time (RT) patch, ensuring deterministic
  task execution within defined deadlines.
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[/GROUP]

[GROUP]
TITLE: Usability & Extensibility
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-CLI
TITLE: Command-Line Interface (CLI)
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall provide a user-friendly command-line interface (CLI) for
  configuring, running, and monitoring simulations.
STATUS: Implemented
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-CUSTOM-COMPONENT-INTEGRATION
TITLE: Custom Component Integration
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall provide a clear and well-documented API for users to
  integrate their own custom simulation components (e.g., written in Rust)
  alongside FMUs.
STATUS: Implemented
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-WEB-INTERFACE
TITLE: Web-Based Management Interface
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall provide an optional web-based interface for remote management
  and monitoring of running simulations. This interface shall allow users to
  control simulation lifecycle (start, stop, pause, resume) and view real-time data.
  Furthermore, it shall present the current running tasks, FMUs, and their data
  dependencies, potentially with a graphical representation such as a causal block
  diagram, leveraging concepts from SysML v2 internal block diagrams.
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[/GROUP]

[GROUP]
TITLE: Toolchain Integration & Workflow
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-MODEL-INTEGRATION
TITLE: Integration with Modeling Environments
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall provide clear guidelines and utilities for integrating
  models developed in external modeling environments (e.g., Simulink, AMESim)
  by supporting their export as FMUs.
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-ONLINE-PARAMETER-TUNING
TITLE: Online Parameter Access and Tuning
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall provide mechanisms to access and modify simulation parameters
  during runtime, enabling online tuning and calibration of models and I/O configurations.
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-SCENARIO-MANAGEMENT
TITLE: Simulation Scenario Management
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall provide capabilities for defining, saving, loading, and
  managing different simulation scenarios, including variations in FMU parameters,
  I/O configurations, and test sequences.
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[/GROUP]

[GROUP]
TITLE: Advanced Simulation Features
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-FAULT-INJECTION
TITLE: Fault Injection Capabilities
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall provide mechanisms to inject faults (e.g., sensor failures,
  communication errors, component malfunctions) into the simulation during runtime
  to support robust testing and validation.
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-XIL-SUPPORT
TITLE: X-in-the-Loop (XiL) Support
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall explicitly support various X-in-the-Loop (XiL) testing methodologies,
  including Model-in-the-Loop (MIL), Software-in-the-Loop (SIL), and Hardware-in-the-Loop (HIL),
  by providing appropriate interfaces and functionalities for each.
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-DISTRIBUTED-SIMULATION
TITLE: Distributed Simulation Support
STATEMENT: >
  The framework shall support the distribution of simulation tasks and FMUs
  across multiple networked computing nodes to enable scaling for large and
  complex simulation scenarios.
REFINES: REQ-FRAMEWORK

[/GROUP]
